            </access>
         </class>
         <class type="4">
            <data version="1">
               <name>AbstractEdit</name>
               <description>This represents a dialog for editing the data of a block. This class provides partial construction of the dialog GUI and handling the events associated with what it creates. An implementation of this class is responsible for handling any apply action and constructing the rest of the GUI. This is a persistent dialog. The GUI of this object is not constructed in this object's constructor since it relies on an interface call as part of its construction process. Instead an initialization method must be called before this object can be used as a dialog.

This class constructs OK, apply, and cancel buttons and handles their clicked events. An interface for applying changes to the block being edited is provided and an implementation must implement this interface. Any exceptions thrown inside the apply interface are caught by this class and reported to the user, not closing its dialog if the OK button was clicked. Because this is a persistent dialog an implementation of this class must define its own unique key using the save settings method of the persistent dialog class.

An implementation of this class must also construct the form portion of this dialog giving user access to the data of the block being edited. This is accomplished through another interface that returns a layout of the form portion that an implementation must implement. The form portion is positioned at the top of the dialog while the buttons this class creates is at the bottom.
</description>
               <qtobject/>
            </data>
            <parent type="13">
               <data version="2">
                  <access>public</access>
                  <class>PersistentDialog</class>
               </data>
            </parent>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>public:</type>
               </data>
               <constructor type="9">
                  <data version="1">
                     <description>Constructs a new abstract edit object with an optional parent. The new abstract edit is not initialized and not ready to be used as a dialog until that method is called.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <explicit/>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>parent</name>
                        <description>Optional parent for this new abstract edit dialog.</description>
                        <type>QWidget*</type>
                        <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </constructor>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>initialize</name>
                     <description>Constructs and initializes the GUI for this abstract edit dialog, making it ready to be used as a GUI dialog window.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Setup this object's buttons saving the returned layout to _buttons_ and then create a new vertical box layout _main_.</operation>
                     <operation>Add the implementation's layout to _main_ by calling the layout interface, then add the layout _buttons_, and then set this dialog's layout to _main_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>protected:</type>
               </data>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>layout</name>
                     <description>This interface is called to return the layout of all GUI elements used by an implementation to edit its block type. All GUI objects are added to this dialog and set as their parent.</description>
                     <type>QLayout*</type>
                     <virtual/>
                     <abstract/>
                     <return_description>Pointer to the layout containing all GUI elements used by an implementation.</return_description>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>apply</name>
                     <description>This interface is called when the user has clicked the apply or OK buttons and expected to update the block an implementation is editing. If an exception is thrown from this interface then the user is informed and the dialog is not closed.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <virtual/>
                     <abstract/>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setDisabled</name>
                     <description>Sets the state of the apply and OK buttons of this dialog to being disabled or enabled.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Set the disabled state of this object's apply and OK buttons based off the given state.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>disabled</name>
                        <description>True to disable apply and OK buttons or false to enable them.</description>
                        <type>bool</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </function>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>private slots:</type>
               </data>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>okClicked</name>
                     <description>Called when this object's OK button is clicked. This tries to apply changes to the implementation's block and if successful closes this dialog.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>applyClicked</name>
                     <description>Called when this object's apply button is clicked. This tries to apply changes to the implementation's block and if successful updates the block's view.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>cancelClicked</name>
                     <description>Called when this object's cancel button is called. This simply closes the dialog without applying anything.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
               </slot>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>private:</type>
               </data>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tryApply</name>
                     <description>Calls this object's apply interface, returning true if it was successful or false if it caught an exception.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <return_description>True is the implementation applied changes successfully or false if an exception was thrown.</return_description>
                     <operation>Call this object's apply interface and return true on success.</operation>
                     <operation>If an exception is caught then report the error to the user and return false on failure.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setupButtons</name>
                     <description>Constructs the three buttons this abstract edit object provides to its implementation, returning the horizontal layout containing the setup buttons.</description>
                     <type>QLayout*</type>
                     <return_description>Horizontal layout containing this object's three buttons.</return_description>
                     <operation>Create a new push button, setting it to this object's OK button and connecting its clicked signal.</operation>
                     <operation>Create a new push button, setting it to this object's apply button and connecting its clicked signal.</operation>
                     <operation>Create a new push button _cancel_, connecting its clicked signal.</operation>
                     <operation>Create a new horizontal layout _ret_, adding the OK button, apply button, stretch, and _cancel_ button in that order.</operation>
                     <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>_ok</name>
                     <description>Pointer to this object's OK button.</description>
                     <type>QPushButton*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>_apply</name>
                     <description>Pointer to this object's apply button.</description>
                     <type>QPushButton*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </access>
         </class>
         <class type="4">
            <data version="1">
               <name>BlockView</name>
               <description>This is the primary view for an open project's block model. This class provides a tree view for the entire block model, a title, a detailed view of the currently selected block, and different actions to edit the underlying block model. Actions provided to the user through a context menu are add, remove, edit, cut, copy, paste, move up, and move down a block. These actions are updated depending on the current block selected. An external link to the context menu of this class is provided. The block model given to this class does not take ownership of it and is not responsible for its deletion.</description>
               <qtobject/>
            </data>
            <parent type="13">
               <data version="2">
                  <access>public</access>
                  <class>QSplitter</class>
               </data>
            </parent>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>public:</type>
               </data>
               <constructor type="9">
                  <data version="1">
                     <description>Constructs a new block view with no model and the optional given parent.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <explicit/>
                     <operation>Setup this object's GUI, restore the state of this qt splitter widget, and update this object's context actions.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>parent</name>
                        <type>QWidget*</type>
                        <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </constructor>
               <destructor type="10">
                  <data version="1">
                     <description>Saves the state of this widget.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <virtual/>
                     <override/>
                     <final/>
                  </data>
               </destructor>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>contextMenu</name>
                     <description>Returns a pointer to this block view object's internal context menu.</description>
                     <type>QMenu*</type>
                     <const/>
                     <return_description>Pointer to this block view object's internal context menu.</return_description>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>canPaste</name>
                     <description>Tests whether the currently copied block can be pasted into the currently selected block. Returns true if it can be pasted or false otherwise.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <const/>
                     <return_description>True if the currently copied block can be pasted into the currently selected block or false if it cannot.</return_description>
                     <operation>If this object has a model, a copy of a block, it's project factory type is equal to the copied block's project type, and the copied block's type is contained within the selected block's build list then return true, else return false.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setModel</name>
                     <description>Sets a new block model for this block view, releasing but not deleting any previous model set to it. This block view does not take ownership of the given model.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Set this object's tree view model to the given block model. Save the given model pointer, a pointer of the given model's block factory, and the new selection model of this object's tree view to this object. Then reset this object's currently selected index to none.</operation>
                     <operation>Connect all selection model and model signals to this object.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>model</name>
                        <description>Pointer to the new block model this block view will display for editing.</description>
                        <type>BlockModel*</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </function>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>public slots:</type>
               </data>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>private slots:</type>
               </data>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>addTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when an add action is triggered. If this object has a model then this inserts a new block of the given type in the currently selected block.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>type</name>
                        <description>The block type created and inserted into this object's model if it has one.</description>
                        <type>int</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>removeTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the remove action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then it is removed from its model.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>If this object's currently selected index is not valid then return.</operation>
                     <operation>Remove this object's currently selected index from its model and then update the currently selected index.</operation>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>editTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the edit action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will open an edit dialog of the index's block.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>If this object's current index is not valid then return.</operation>
                     <operation>Create an abstract block pointer _pointer_, set it to this object's current index block, and then create a new edit dialog _edit_ from _pointer_. If the returned edit dialog is null then return.</operation>
                     <operation>Initialize _edit_, set its icon to the block icon of _pointer_, set its title using the block type name of _pointer_, modal execute the edit dialog, and then update this object's current detailed view of the block that was just edited.</operation>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>cutTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the cut action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will cut it from this object's model.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>If this object's current index is valid then delete any current block copy, cut the current index's block from the model and set it as this object's new copy, update the current index, and update this object's context menu.</operation>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>copyTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the copy action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will copy it from this object's model.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>If this object's current index is valid then delete any current block copy, copy the current index's block from the model and set it as this object's new copy, and update this object's actions.</operation>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pasteTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the paste action is triggered. If this object can paste its copied block into its model then it does so.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>moveUpTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the move up action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will move it up by one.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>moveDownTriggered</name>
                     <description>Called when the move down action is triggered. If this object has a valid current index then this will move it down by one.</description>
                     <type></type>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>selectionModelChanged</name>
                     <description>Called when this object's selection model has changed. This determines its object's new current index, updating its view and context menu afterwords.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>Update this object's current index based off its model's new selection, using the first index as its new current index. If there are no selected indexes then set the current index as invalid.</operation>
                     <operation>Update this object's view and context menu.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>selected</name>
                        <description>List of indexes that have been selected by the user.</description>
                        <type>const QItemSelection&amp;</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>deselected</name>
                        <description>Unused list of indexes that have been deselected by the user.</description>
                        <type>const QItemSelection&amp;</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>modelDestroyed</name>
                     <description>Called when this object's block model is about to be deleted. This clears its object's view to a null state and all internal pointers.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>Clear this object's title icon and text.</operation>
                     <operation>Set this object's model, factory, and selection models to null. Set this object's current index to an invalid one.</operation>
                     <operation>Update this object's detailed view and context menu.</operation>
                  </data>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>modelDataChanged</name>
                     <description>Called when data in this object's block model has changed. If this object's current index is the one updated then this updates its object's view depending on the given roles.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>If the given top left index is equal to this object's current index and the current index is not valid then update this object's title if needed, detailed view if needed, and context menu.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>topLeft</name>
                        <description>The top left index of the rectangle of indexes whose data has changed.</description>
                        <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>bottomRight</name>
                        <description>The bottom right index of the rectangle of indexes whose data has changed. This is not used in this view because only one index can change at a time.</description>
                        <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>roles</name>
                        <description>The list of data roles that has changed.</description>
                        <type>const QVector&lt;int>&amp;</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </slot>
               <slot type="7">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>contextMenuRequested</name>
                     <description>Called when this object's tree view is requesting a context menu because of a right mouse click. This updates its object's current index based off the mouse click position and executes its object's context menu.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <operation>Update this object's current index to the one located where the mouse event occurred, updating the view and context menu afterwords.</operation>
                     <operation>Modal execute this object's context menu.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>position</name>
                        <description>The relative position within this object's tree view where the mouse event occurred.</description>
                        <type>const QPoint&amp;</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </slot>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>private:</type>
               </data>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>updateView</name>
                     <description>Updates this object's detailed view using its current index. This does not update this object's title.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Delete the current view. If there is no currently selected block then set the detailed view pointer to null and return.</operation>
                     <operation>Create an abstract block pointer _pointer_, setting it to this object's currently selected block. Call the abstract block's make view interface, saving the returned detailed view to this object. If the detailed view returned is a null pointer then throw an exception.</operation>
                     <operation>Set this object's scroll area widget to this object's new detailed view widget and update this object's title with the abstract block _pointer_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>updateIndex</name>
                     <description>Updates this object's current index using its selection model. This does not update this object's actions or context menu.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Get the list of selected indexes from this object's selection model. If the returned list is not empty then set the first index to this object's current index, else set this object's current index as invalid.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>updateContextMenu</name>
                     <description>Updates this object's context menu based off its current index, updating its actions beforehand as well.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Update this object's actions and clear its add menu.</operation>
                     <operation>Iterate through all of this object's add actions and add them to its add menu. If the add menu is empty then disable it or enable it otherwise.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>updateActions</name>
                     <description>Updates this object's list of actions, enabling or disabling the primary ones and rebuilding the list of add actions based off the current index.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Update the add actions list based off this object's current index.</operation>
                     <operation>Enable or disable this object's remove, edit, copy, cut, move up, and move down actions based off its current index being valid or not.</operation>
                     <operation>Enable or disable the paste action based off the can paste method and the add menu based off if this object has a model or not.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>updateAddActions</name>
                     <description>Updates the add actions list of this object, clearing out the old list and building it again based on this object's current index.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Delete all add actions on this object's list and clear it. If this object does not have a model then return.</operation>
                     <operation>Iterate through the build list of the block this object's current index points to, adding a new action to the add actions list for adding it. Connect each new action to the add triggered slot using a lambda to remember the block type to be added if it is triggered.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>updateTitle</name>
                     <description>Updates this object's title bar based on using the given block.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Clear this object's title icon and text labels, setting them to the icon and name of the given block.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>block</name>
                        <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>restoreSettings</name>
                     <description>Restores this object's Qt splitter state using Qt settings.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Create a qt settings object and restore the state of this object's qt splitter using this class's key.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>saveSettings</name>
                     <description>Saves this object's Qt splitter state using Qt settings.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Create a qt settings object and save the state of this object's qt splitter using this class's key.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setupGui</name>
