         <class type="4">
            <data version="1">
               <name>AboutDialog</name>
               <description>This is a simple dialog that presents information about this program. The only functionality is to simply close it by clicking OK.</description>
               <qtobject/>
            </data>
            <parent type="13">
               <data version="2">
                  <access>public</access>
                  <class>PersistentDialog</class>
               </data>
            </parent>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>public:</type>
               </data>
               <constructor type="9">
                  <data version="1">
                     <description>Constructs a new about dialog with the given optional parent.</description>
                     <type></type>
                     <explicit/>
                     <operation>Setup this object's GUI and set the dialog window's title.</operation>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>parent</name>
                        <description>Pointer to this new about dialog object's parent or null for no parent.</description>
                        <type>QWidget*</type>
                        <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </constructor>
            </access>
            <access type="5">
               <data version="1">
                  <type>private:</type>
               </data>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setupGui</name>
                     <description>Constructs all GUI elements for this new about dialog.</description>
                     <type>void</type>
                     <operation>Create a new vertical box layout _layout_, adding the top and bottom layout sections of this object's GUI in that order.</operation>
                     <operation>Set this object's layout to _layout_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setupTop</name>
                     <description>Constructs the top part of this object's GUI consisting of an image to the left and description to the right, returning the layout.</description>
                     <type>QLayout*</type>
                     <return_description>Pointer to layout of the top section of this object's GUI.</return_description>
                     <operation>Create a new label _image_, setting its pixmap to the program's icon scaled to the correct dimensions.</operation>
                     <operation>Create a new horizontal box layout _ret_, adding the _image_ label and then the layout returned from this object's setup text method.</operation>
                     <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setupText</name>
                     <description>Constructs the rich text displayed in the top right of this object's GUI, returning a pointer to the widget.</description>
                     <type>QWidget*</type>
                     <return_description>Pointer to the widget of rich text displayed in the top right of this object's GUI.</return_description>
                     <operation>Create a new label _ret_, setting its alignment, word wrapping, text format, and margin.</operation>
                     <operation>Create a new qt file device _file_ and open the about HTML file with it. If opening the file fails then throw an exception.</operation>
                     <operation>Set the text of the created label _ret_ with the contents of _file_, replacing the keys for this program version and the Qt version.</operation>
                     <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <function type="2">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>setupBottom</name>
                     <description>Constructs the bottom part of this object's GUI which simply consists of an OK button on the bottom right, returning the layout.</description>
                     <type>QLayout*</type>
                     <return_description>Pointer to layout of the bottom section of this object's GUI.</return_description>
                     <operation>Create a new push button _ok_, connecting its clicked signal to close this dialog.</operation>
                     <operation>Create a new horizontal box layout _ret_, adding a stretch and then the _ok_ button.</operation>
                     <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
                  </data>
               </function>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>_iconSize</name>
                     <description>The width and height of the program's icon displayed in the top left of this object's GUI.</description>
                     <constexpr/>
                     <static/>
                     <type>int</type>
                     <initializer>128</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </access>
         </class>
      </namespace>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>Singleton</name>
            <description>This template can be inherited by any class that wants to be a singleton class. Any class that uses this template to be a singleton class must have a default constructor. A singleton class is a class that has only one global instance for the entire program.</description>
         </data>
         <typeList type="15">
            <data version="1">
               <name>Custom</name>
            </data>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>T&amp;</type>
               </data>
            </type>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>T*</type>
               </data>
            </type>
         </typeList>
         <template type="3">
            <data version="1">
               <name>T</name>
               <description>This must be the class type that inherits this class.</description>
               <type>class</type>
            </data>
         </template>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>instance</name>
                  <description>Returns the single global instance of the singleton class that inherits from this template class.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>T&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to singleton class instance.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the global pointer is null then make a new instance of the singleton class with its default constructor and set the global pointer to this new instance.</operation>
                  <operation>Return a reference to the global singleton class instance.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_instance</name>
                  <description>Pointer to the global single instance of the singleton class that inherits from this template class.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>T*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>SingletonFactory</name>
            <description>This template can be inherited by any class that wants to be a singleton factory. A singleton class is a class that has only one global instance for the entire program. The global instance can be set to a new instance at anytime, deleting any existing instance. The is most commonly used with abstract factories that have a single global instance in a program.</description>
         </data>
         <typeList type="15">
            <data version="1">
               <name>Custom</name>
            </data>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>T&amp;</type>
               </data>
            </type>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>T*</type>
               </data>
            </type>
         </typeList>
         <template type="3">
            <data version="1">
               <name>T</name>
               <description>This must be the class type that inherits this class.</description>
               <type>class</type>
            </data>
         </template>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>instance</name>
                  <description>Returns the single global instance of the singleton factory that inherits from this template class. If an instance has never been set then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>T&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to singleton factory instance.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the global pointer is null then throw an exception, else return a reference to the global singleton factory instance.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setInstance</name>
                  <description>Sets a new instance of the singleton factory that inherits this template class with the given pointer. If an instance already exists the old one is deleted and replaced by the new one given.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Delete any singleton factory instance pointed to by the global pointer and set the global pointer to the new singleton factory instance.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>instance</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the new global instance for the singleton factory inherited from this template class.</description>
                     <type>T*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_instance</name>
                  <description>Pointer to the global single instance of the singleton factory that inherits from this template class.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>T*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>DomElementReader</name>
            <description>This is a helper class that makes is easier to read information stored in an XML element. This primarily helps with finding child elements and extracting information enclosed within them. This also helps with getting attributes in text or integer form and throwing exceptions if they don't exist. For searching child elements this class works by adding matches that will be looked for when the XML element given to this class is read. When a match is found the variable passed to the match is set to the value of the matched child element. This class is designed to only read its given XML element once and then be destroyed.</description>
         </data>
         <typeList type="15">
            <data version="1">
               <name>Custom</name>
            </data>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>Match*</type>
               </data>
            </type>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>Type</type>
               </data>
            </type>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>QHash&lt;QString,Match*></type>
               </data>
            </type>
         </typeList>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>Constructs a new element reader with the given XML element that this object can read.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>element</name>
                     <description>The XML element this object will read.</description>
                     <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </constructor>
            <destructor type="10">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>Deletes all allocates matches in the lookup list.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
            </destructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>attribute</name>
                  <description>Returns the text value of the given attribute from this reader's element. If no attribute exists with the given name and it is required then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Value of the attribute with the given name.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the attribute with the given name is not found then continue. If the attribute is required then throw an exception, else return an empty string.</operation>
                  <operation>Return the value of the attribute with the given name.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>name</name>
                     <description>Name of attribute whose value is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if an exception should be thrown if the attribute is not found otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>attributeToInt</name>
                  <description>Returns the integer value of the given attribute from this reader's element. If no attribute exists with the given name or the value is not an integer, and the attribute is required, then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Value of the attribute with the given name.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the attribute with the given name is not found then continue. If the attribute is required then throw an exception, else return 0.</operation>
                  <operation>Read in the value of the attribute with the given name as an integer to _ret_. If reading the value as an integer fails then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>name</name>
                     <description>Name of attribute whose integer value is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if an exception should be thrown if the attribute is not found or failed to read as an integer otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>set</name>
                  <description>Set a new child element match with the given tag name. When this reader reads its element, if a child element is found with the given tag name then the string pointed to by the given pointer will be set to the matched child element's text.</description>
                  <type>DomElementReader&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to this element reader.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>Tag name to find in this reader's child elements.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer to a string that will be set if a child element is matched.</description>
                     <type>QString*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if this match is required otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>set</name>
                  <description>Set a new child element match with the given tag name. When this reader reads its element, if a child element is found with the given tag name then the integer pointed to by the given pointer will be set to the matched child element's text. If the matched element's text cannot be converted to an integer then an exception will be thrown.</description>
                  <type>DomElementReader&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to this element reader.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>Tag name to find in this reader's child elements.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer to an integer that will be set if a child element is matched.</description>
                     <type>int*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if this match is required otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>set</name>
                  <description>Set a new child element match with the given tag name. When this reader reads its element, if a child element is found with the given tag name then the boolean pointed to by the given pointer will be set to true.</description>
                  <type>DomElementReader&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to this element reader.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>Tag name to find in this reader's child elements.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer to a boolean that will be set to true if a child element is matched.</description>
                     <type>bool*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if this match is required otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>set</name>
                  <description>Set a new child element match with the given tag name. When this reader reads its element, if a child element is found with the given tag name then the XML element pointed to by the given pointer will be set to the matched child element.</description>
                  <type>DomElementReader&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to this element reader.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>Tag name to find in this reader's child elements.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer to a XML element that will be set to a child element is matched.</description>
                     <type>QDomElement*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if this match is required otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>set</name>
                  <description>Set a new child element match with the given tag name. When this reader reads its element, if a child element is found with the given tag name then it is appended to the list of elements pointed to by the match.</description>
                  <type>DomElementReader&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to this element reader.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>Tag name to find in this reader's child elements.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer to a list of XML elements that will have any matched child elements appended to it.</description>
                     <type>QList&lt;QDomElement>*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if this match is required otherwise false.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                     <initializer>true</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>read</name>
                  <description>Reads this reader's XML element for child elements, finding any matches set before this is called. Before reading begins this clears all variables pointed to by the list of set matches.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Clear all variables pointed to by this reader's list of matches.</operation>
                  <operation>Iterate through all child nodes of this reader's XML element. If the node is an element and its name matches one of the set matches then read in the match with the matched element.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>allRequiredFound</name>
                  <description>Tests if all required matches found at least one match after called the read method.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>True if all required matches were found or false otherwise.</return_description>
                  <operation>Iterate through all matches. If a match is found that was not read then return false, else if all matches were read then return true.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <class type="4">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>Match</name>
                  <description>This holds a single match for an XML element reader.</description>
               </data>
               <access type="5">
                  <data version="1">
                     <type>public:</type>
                  </data>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>_type</name>
                        <description>The type of match this is.</description>
                        <type>Type</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>_data</name>
                        <description>The pointer to the variable for this match.</description>
                        <type>void*</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
                  <variable type="1">
                     <data version="1">
                        <name>_read</name>
                        <description>The read state of this match. True if this data has been read otherwise false.</description>
                        <type>bool</type>
                     </data>
                  </variable>
               </access>
            </class>
            <enumeration type="11">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>Type</name>
                  <description>Defines all the possible match types that can be set in an element reader.</description>
                  <class/>
               </data>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>String</name>
                     <description>Defines a match that sets a string.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>Number</name>
                     <description>Defines a match that sets an integer.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>Boolean</name>
                     <description>Defines a match that sets a boolean.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>Element</name>
                     <description>Defines a match that sets another element.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>ElementList</name>
                     <description>Defines a match that adds to an element list.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
            </enumeration>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>read</name>
                  <description>Reads in a single match found with the given match and given XML element, marking the match as being read.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Determine the match type of the given match. Assign the match's data based off its type, taking the value of the given element if required. If the match type is an integer and the given element cannot be read as an integer then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Mark the given match as being read.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>match</name>
                     <description>The match that was matched with the given element.</description>
                     <type>Match*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>element</name>
                     <description>The element whose tag name was matched with the given match.</description>
                     <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>append</name>
                  <description>Inserts a new match to the lookup hash table of matches for this element reader. If a tag name already exists then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>DomElementReader&amp;</type>
                  <return_description>Reference to this element reader.</return_description>
                  <operation>If a match already exists in this element reader's lookup hash table with the given tag name then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Add a new match to this element reader's lookup hash table using the given tag name as the key. Use the inverse of the required condition for the new match's read condition which marks any matches that are not required as read.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>Tag name for the new match that is inserted.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the variable that is used for the given match that is inserted.</description>
                     <type>void*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>The type for the given match that is inserted.</description>
                     <type>Type</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>required</name>
                     <description>True if this match is required or false otherwise.</description>
                     <type>bool</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>clear</name>
                  <description>Clears the variables of all matches to default values. For integers that is 0 and for boolean that is false.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Iterate through all matches of this reader. Set the match's data to its default type based off the match's type. For strings, elements, and element lists that is calling their clear method. For numbers that is setting it to 0. For booleans that is setting it to false.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_element</name>
                  <description>The XML element that this element reader reads the direct children of with the read method and extracts arguments from.</description>
                  <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_lookup</name>
                  <description>The hash table used to store all matches and look them up by their tag name for this element reader used when reading the child elements of this reader's XML element.</description>
                  <type>QHash&lt;QString,Match*></type>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>AbstractBlock</name>
            <description>This represents a single block of data in the reference system. It conforms to a parent child relationship where each block can have any number of children that are also blocks. The children are structured in an ordered list so they can be represented as a tree like structure in a view. Blocks also spawn the GUI elements that represent their models. Copying of blocks is also performed with other virtual interface functions. Many helper functions are available to navigate the tree structure of children and parents. Blocks are identified by a type which is an integer value that must be unique among all block types of a project type supplied by the block factory. Blocks are saved and opened using XML elements. The data for these XML elements have version numbers so later versions of this software can identify and read previous versions of XML elements.</description>
            <qtobject/>
         </data>
         <typeList type="15">
            <data version="1">
               <name>Custom</name>
            </data>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>T*</type>
               </data>
            </type>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>const T*</type>
               </data>
            </type>
            <type type="16">
               <data version="0">
                  <type>QList&lt;T*></type>
               </data>
            </type>
         </typeList>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>QObject</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>type</name>
                  <description>This interface returns this block's type.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>This block's type.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>factory</name>
                  <description>This interface returns a reference to this block's factory which produces all block types for this project type.</description>
                  <type>const AbstractBlockFactory&amp;</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Reference to block factory.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>name</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the name of this block. The name is used to display the block as text in a tree view and as a title when selected.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>The name of this block.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>icon</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the icon of this block. The icon is displayed in a tree view of this block and its title if selected.</description>
                  <type>QIcon</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>The icon of this block.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>buildList</name>
                  <description>This interface returns a list of types that this block can contain as children. If the same type is listed more than once any repeated occurrences are ignored and the type is allowed to be this block's parent.</description>
                  <type>QList&lt;int></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>List of allowed types this block can contain as children.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeView</name>
                  <description>This interface returns a View that provides a detailed read only GUI representation of this block's data.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;QWidget></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>New GUI view that represents this block's data.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeEdit</name>
                  <description>This interface returns a editable GUI widget that provides the ability to edit this block's data.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;::Gui::AbstractEdit></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>New editable GUI widget to edit this block's data.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeCopy</name>
                  <description>This interface makes an exact copy of this block. A default implementation of this interface is given that uses other virtual functions to create a copy of this block. The new block returned has no parent.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Exact copy of this block's data as a new block.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a new empty block _ret_ that is the same type as this block. Copy this block's children and implementation data to _ret_.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>root</name>
                  <description>This returns the root block in this block's tree structure. The root block is the common parent of all other blocks that has no parent itself.</description>
                  <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  <return_description>Pointer to the root block.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create an abstract block pointer _root_ with it pointing to this abstract block. While _root_ has a parent set its pointer to its parent.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _root_.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>root</name>
                  <description>This returns the root block in this block's tree structure. The root block is the common parent of all other blocks that has no parent itself.</description>
                  <type>const AbstractBlock*</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Read only pointer to the root block.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a constant abstract block pointer _root_ with it pointing to this abstract block. While _root_ has a parent set its pointer to its parent.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _root_.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>parent</name>
                  <description>This returns a pointer to the parent of this block. If this block is the root block then null is returned.</description>
                  <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>If this block is the root then a null pointer, else a pointer to this block's parent.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>size</name>
                  <description>This returns the number of children this block contains.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Number of children this block contains.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>list</name>
                  <description>This returns a read only reference to this block's list of children blocks. The list is a list of pointers to all child blocks.</description>
                  <type>const QList&lt;AbstractBlock*>&amp;</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Reference to this block's list of children.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>indexOf</name>
                  <description>This gets the index where the child with the given pointer is stored in this block's list of children. If no child with the given pointer is found then -1 is returned.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>If a match is found then the index of the child with the given pointer, else -1.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>pointer</name>
                     <description>Pointer of child block to match in this block's list and return its index.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>get</name>
                  <description>This returns a pointer to this block's child with the given index. If the index is out of range an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to this block's child with given index.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is out of range then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Return a pointer to this block's child with the given index.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>Index of the child whose pointer is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>containsType</name>
                  <description>Tests if this block contains any children of the given type.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>True if this block contains any children of the given type, else false.</return_description>
                  <operation>Iterate through list of this block's children. If a child matches the given type then return true.</operation>
                  <operation>Return false because no child was found with the given type.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>The block type to search for within this block's list of children.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>containsType</name>
                  <description>Tests if this block contains any children of any type given.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>True if this block contains any children of any type given, else false.</return_description>
                  <operation>Iterate through list of this block's children. If a child matches the given type then return true.</operation>
                  <operation>Return false because no child was found with the given type.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>types</name>
                     <description>List of block types to search for within this block's list of children.</description>
                     <type>const QList&lt;int>&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeListOfType</name>
                  <description>Build a list of this block's children that matches the given type. The returned list has no other copies.</description>
                  <type>QList&lt;T*></type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>List of this block's children that is given type.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a new list of pointers _ret_ of the given template type. Iterate through the list of this block's children. If a child matches the given type then append its pointer to _ret_.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
               <template type="3">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>T</name>
                     <description>The child class type that is matched.</description>
                     <type>class</type>
                  </data>
               </template>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>The type whose matches are added to the list.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>cast</name>
                  <description>This casts this block to a specific block type. If the given type does not match this block's type then a null pointer is returned. If this object fails to cast as the requested type an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>const T*</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>If successful then a read only pointer of requested cast type, else a null pointer.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given type to cast does not match this block's type then return a null pointer.</operation>
                  <operation>Cast this block's pointer to the requested class type and return the cast pointer. If the cast fails then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <template type="3">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>T</name>
                     <description>The class type that is cast.</description>
                     <type>class</type>
                  </data>
               </template>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>toType</name>
                     <description>The block type that this block is cast to.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>cast</name>
                  <description>This casts this block to a specific block type. If the given type does not match this block's type then a null pointer is returned. If this object fails to cast as the requested type an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>T*</type>
                  <return_description>If successful then a pointer of requested cast type, else a null pointer.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given type to cast does not match this block's type then return a null pointer.</operation>
                  <operation>Cast this block's pointer to the requested class type and return the cast pointer. If the cast fails then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <template type="3">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>T</name>
                     <description>The class type that is cast.</description>
                     <type>class</type>
                  </data>
               </template>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>toType</name>
                     <description>The block type that this block is cast to.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>moveUp</name>
                  <description>Moves the child block with the given index up the list by one where the very top of the list is index 0. If the given index is already at the top of the list or out of range then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given index is at the top of the list or is out of range then return, else swap the child with the given index with the child just above it and call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child moved interface and continue calling the next parent's child moved interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child block moved up by one.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>moveDown</name>
                  <description>Moves the child block with the given index down the list by one where the very top of the list is index 0. If the given index is already at the bottom of the list or out of range then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given index is at the top of the list or is out of range then return, else swap the child with the given index with the child just below it and call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child moved interface and continue calling the next parent's child moved interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child block moved down by one.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>insert</name>
                  <description>Inserts a new child block into this block's list of children at the given index. If the given index is less than 0 it is prepended to this block's list, else if the given index is greater than this block's list size then it is appended. If the given pointer to the new block is null or it is a type this block cannot contain then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given child pointer is null or its type is not contained in this blocks build list then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Insert the new block into this block's list of children at the given index, releasing it from its smart pointer and setting this block as its parent. Call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child added interface and continue calling the next parent's child added interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index where the new block is inserted.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the new block that is inserted as this block's child.</description>
                     <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock>&amp;&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>take</name>
                  <description>Takes the child block at the given index this block contains. The child block returned no longer has a parent. If the index is out of range then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <return_description>Pointer to child that was taken from this block.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is out of range then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Remove the child at the given index from this block's list of children saving its pointer to the smart pointer _ret_. Call the child removed interface and call the notify modified method.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with this block call its child removed interface with _ret_ and continue calling the next parent's child removed interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child that is taken.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>remove</name>
                  <description>Removes the child block at the given index, deleting it and any children it may contain. If the given index is out of range then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index of the child that is removed and deleted.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>read</name>
                  <description>Reads in block data from an XML element. This clears any existing data this block contains, including the removal and deletion of all existing children. This recursively adds any children contained in the XML reading in their data from child XML elements.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Delete and clear any existing children this block may contain.</operation>
                  <operation>Read in the data child element from the given element, calling the read data interface to read in the data. If the data element could not be found in the XML element then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Read in all child elements of the given element that match block children tag names and add them to this block's list of children, creating a new child for each one and calling their read function.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>element</name>
                     <description>The XML element that stores block data this block reads as input.</description>
                     <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>write</name>
                  <description>Writes out this blocks data as an XML element. This includes all children as child XML elements which have their write functions called recursively.</description>
                  <type>QDomElement</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>XML element that stores this block's data and all children underneath it.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a new XML element _data_ created by calling the write data interface for writing the data of this block's type as an XML element. Add the version number attribute to _data_ using the write version interface to set its value.</operation>
                  <operation>Create a new XML element _ret_. Append the _data_ element to _ret_. Iterate through this block's list of children, calling their write method and appending the returned child element to _ret_.</operation>
                  <operation>Return _ret_.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>document</name>
                     <type>QDomDocument&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>signals:</type>
            </data>
            <signal type="8">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>modified</name>
                  <description>Signals that a child block of this block has been modified. The given child block could be any depth below this block. Only the root block emits this signal.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
            </signal>
            <signal type="8">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>nameModified</name>
                  <description>Signals that a child block of this block with the given pointer has modified its name. The given child block could be any depth below this block. Only the root block emits this signal.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer of the child whose name has changed.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </signal>
            <signal type="8">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>bodyModified</name>
                  <description>Signals that a child block of this block with the given pointer has modified its body. The given child block could be any depth below this block. Only the root block emits this signal.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </signal>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>protected:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>readData</name>
                  <description>This interface reads in the data for this block from the given XML element and version number.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <abstract/>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>element</name>
                     <description>The XML element used to read in this blocks data.</description>
                     <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>version</name>
                     <description>The version of the data stored in the XML.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>writeVersion</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the current version number of XML elements written for this block type.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Current version number.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>writeData</name>
                  <description>This interface returns a XML element containing the data for this block using the current version number. Attributes should never be used with this element because the block system already uses one for the version number.</description>
                  <type>QDomElement</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>XML element containing the data of this block.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>document</name>
                     <description>XML document to use for creating new elements.</description>
                     <type>QDomDocument&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeBlank</name>
                  <description>This interface makes a new block object of this block's type with no data and returns a pointer to the new block.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to the newly created block.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>copyDataFrom</name>
                  <description>This interface copies all data from the given block to this block, overwriting any data this block may already contain. This does not copy any children.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <abstract/>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>other</name>
                     <description>The other block whose data will be copied.</description>
                     <type>const AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>childNameModified</name>
                  <description>This interface is called whenever a child below this block has modified its name and keeps calling this interface the next block parent until this returns false. The default implementation does nothing and returns false.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <return_description>True if this interface should be called again on this blocks parent or false otherwise.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the child block that has modified its name.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>childAdded</name>
                  <description>This interface is called whenever a new child below this block has been added and keeps calling this interface on the next block parent until this returns false. The default implementation does nothing and returns false.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <return_description>True if this interface should be called again on this blocks parent or false otherwise.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the child block that been added to its new parent block.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>childRemoved</name>
                  <description>This interface is called whenever an existing child below this block has been removed and keeps calling this interface on the next block parent until this returns false. The default implementation does nothing and returns false.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <return_description>True if this interface should be called again on this blocks parent or false otherwise.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the child block that has been removed from its former parent block. This object can be deleted right after this call.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>childMoved</name>
                  <description>This interface is called whenever an existing child below this block has been moved and keeps calling this interface on the next block parent until this returns false. The default implementation does nothing and returns false.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <return_description>True if this interface should be called again on this blocks parent or false otherwise.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the child block that has been moved in its parent's list of children.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>notifyModified</name>
                  <description>Notifies this block has been modified by finding its root block and emitting its modified signal.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Find the root block of this block and emit its modified signal.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>notifyNameModified</name>
                  <description>Notifies this block's name has been modified by finding its root block and emitting its name modified signal. If this is called by a root block an exception is thrown because the root has no name.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Create a pointer _root_ to the parent of this block. If the returned pointer is null then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Starting with _root_ call its child name modified interface and continue calling the next parent's child name modified interface until the interface returns false or the root block is reached.</operation>
                  <operation>Find the root block of _root_ and emit its name modified signal with this block's pointer.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>notifyBodyModified</name>
                  <description>Notifies this block's body has been modified by finding its root block and emitting its name modified signal. If this is called by a root block an exception is thrown because the root has no body.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Create a pointer _root_ to the parent of this block. If the returned pointer is null then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Find the root block of _root_ and emit its body modified signal with this block's pointer.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeElement</name>
                  <description>Makes a new XML element with the given tag name and text value enclosed within the new element.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>QDomElement</type>
                  <return_description>New XML element with the given tag name and text.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a new XML element with the given tag name, setting its text to the given text, and then returning it.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>document</name>
                     <description>The XML document used to create the new XML element.</description>
                     <type>QDomDocument&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>tagName</name>
                     <description>The tag name for the new XML element.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>text</name>
                     <description>The text enclosed within the new XML element.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>copyChildren</name>
                  <description>Copies all children from the given block and appends the copies to the list of this block's children. This does not remove any previous children already part of this block.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Iterate through all the children of the given block. Make a copy of each child, appending them to this block's list of children.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>Pointer to block whose children are copied.</description>
                     <type>const AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setParent</name>
                  <description>Sets this block's parent to the given block, adding it to its new parent's list with the given index. If the index is less than 1 it is prepended, else if it is greater than the size of the list it is appended. This will remove any previous parent this block may have had. The new parent can be a null pointer which means this block will have no parent.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the new parent for this block.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index where this block will be added to its new parent's list.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                     <initializer>-1</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>readChild</name>
                  <description>Creates a new child reading it in from the given XML element. The new child is then appended to this block's list of children.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Read in the type attribute from the given child element. If the read in type is out of range of possible types for this project type then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Create a new block with the given type and call its read method with the given child XML element, appending it to this blocks list of children.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>element</name>
                     <description>XML element used to read in the new child.</description>
                     <type>const QDomElement&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_versionTag</name>
                  <description>The name for version attributes.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>const char*</type>
                  <initializer>"version"</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_dataTag</name>
                  <description>The tag name for data elements.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>const char*</type>
                  <initializer>"data"</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_typeTag</name>
                  <description>The name for type attributes.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>const char*</type>
                  <initializer>"type"</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_children</name>
                  <description>Pointer list of this block's children.</description>
                  <type>QList&lt;AbstractBlock*></type>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>AbstractBlockFactory</name>
            <description>This represents the factory that can produce blocks for a specific project type. There should only be one instance of this class for each project type. Along with making new blocks this factory also gives basic information about each block type such as its display and element names. To maintain backwards compatibility all previously defined block types must maintain the specific integer that defines them.</description>
         </data>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <destructor type="10">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>Virtual destructor so implemented classes have their destructor called correctly.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <default/>
                  <virtual/>
               </data>
            </destructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>type</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the project type of this block factory.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Project type.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>size</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the number of block types that exist for this factory. Block types must be defined for all integers from 0 to one less than the number of block types returned by this interface.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Number of block types that exist for this factory.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>name</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the display name for the given block type.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Display name for the given block type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Block type whose display name is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>elementName</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the element name for the given block type. The element name is used as the tag name in XML elements for reading/writing of blocks.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Element name for the given block type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Block type whose element name is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeBlock</name>
                  <description>This interface makes a new block of the given type and returns its pointer. The new block is expected to have a null data state.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to new block with given type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Block type which is made and returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeRootBlock</name>
                  <description>This interface makes a new root block and returns its pointer. The root block is used as the root block for all projects of this project type. The new root block is expected to have a null data state.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to new root block for this project type.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>AbstractParser</name>
            <description>This represents a parser object which takes in a single source code file to parse and outputs the results, overwriting the file if the results are different from the original contents. It can contain child parser objects which can be used for parsing segments of the source file allowing for specializing of parsing within segments of the file. Children parser objects will write lines to its root parser object. This allows for parsing the same file but using different parser object types when different parts of the file are reached. This class is designed to only have implementations executed once and then destroyed.</description>
            <qtobject/>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>QObject</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This constructs a new parser object that will be a root or primary parser. This means this parser will be assumed to be the root parser of a source file.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <explicit/>
                  <operation>Allocate new resources required for this new parser object.</operation>
               </data>
            </constructor>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This constructs a new parser object that is a child of another parser object. This sets up this object to use the resources of its root parser object.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <explicit/>
                  <operation>Set this object's parent as the given parent parser, add this parser to its parent's list of children, and set this object's root parser pointer.</operation>
                  <operation>Set all resource pointers to point to this object's root parser resources.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>The parent parser object for this new parser object.</description>
                     <type>AbstractParser*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </constructor>
            <destructor type="10">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This deletes the dynamically allocated resources if this parser if it is the root. If this is a child parser then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <operation>If this is a root parser then delete all allocated resources else do nothing.</operation>
               </data>
            </destructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>execute</name>
                  <description>This parses the given file using this parser as the root parser. If this is a child parser then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If this is not a root parser then return.</operation>
                  <operation>Set the read line index to the beginning, call the initialize interface, and read in all lines of the source file.</operation>
                  <operation>Process the input lines, output lines, and then write the output to the source file.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>file</name>
                     <description>Qt file handle to the file that is parsed.</description>
                     <type>QFile*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>protected:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>initialize</name>
                  <description>This interface initializes this parser. The default implementation does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <virtual/>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>readLine</name>
                  <description>This interface is called for each line of the input source file, reading in all lines of the file until the end is reached or this returns false. If false is returned and this is a child parser then this interface keeps getting called on this object's parent parser under the same conditions. A different function is used to signal this parser should start feeding input lines to a child parser this parser contains.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>True signals this interface should continue being called on lines else false signals this parser is finished processing input.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>line</name>
                     <description>The line from the source file that is processed.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeOutput</name>
                  <description>This interface creates the output lines for the source file, using the add and indent functions to do so.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <abstract/>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>stepIntoChild</name>
                  <description>Signals this parser that the given child parser should be used for calling the interface for reading lines until it returns false or the last line is processed. If the given parser is not a direct child of this parser then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given parser object's parent is not this parser then throw an exception, else set the internal child pointer signal variable to the given parser.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the child parser whose interface for reading lines will be called from now on.</description>
                     <type>AbstractParser*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>indent</name>
                  <description>Returns the indent, in spaces, that is prepended to each line added to the output.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Number of spaces prepended to each added line of output.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setIndent</name>
                  <description>Sets the indent, in spaces, that is prepended to each line added to output.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given indent is less than 0 then throw an exception, else set the root parser object's indent to the new value given.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>indent</name>
                     <description>The new indent value in spaces.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>add</name>
                  <description>Adds the given line as a new line to output, appending it to the end of any existing lines. The line is prepended with a number of spaces equal to the indent.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Prepend the given line with spaces equal to the indent of the root parser.</operation>
                  <operation>Append the given line to the list of output lines of the root parser.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>line</name>
                     <description>The line that is prepended with the indent and appended to the output.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>add</name>
                  <description>Appends multiple lines to the output, each one being prepended with spaces equal to the indent.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>lines</name>
                     <description>Lines that are appended to the output.</description>
                     <type>const QStringList&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>add</name>
                  <description>Appends the given number of blank lines to the output. If the given number is less than 1 then nothing is added to the output.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>count</name>
                     <description>The number of blank lines added to the output.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>read</name>
                  <description>Reads in the source file, splitting them into lines, and prepares the output.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Read all contents of the given file, storing it as this object's original contents. If reading in the file failed then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Split the original content by line and save it to this object's list of input lines to be processed.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>file</name>
                     <description>The file used as input.</description>
                     <type>QFile*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>processInput</name>
                  <description>Processes the input of the source file, using the read line interface for processing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>While the root parser object's index is not at the end of the input line list continue. Call the read line interface with the next input line to process. If the interface returns false then return. If the step into child function was called and set the child pointer signal then call the child's process input function and then set the child pointer signal back to null.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>processOutput</name>
                  <description>Processes the output by calling the make output interface.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Clear the root parser object's output string list, set its indent to 0, and call the make output interface.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>write</name>
                  <description>Write the processed output to the given file if, after joining the output lines, it is different from the original. If the output is the same as the original then this does nothing.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Join the root parser object's output lines into the string _newSource_.</operation>
                  <operation>If _newSource_ is different from the root parser object's original file content then continue. Truncate the given file to 0 size and then write out the contents of _newSource_ to the given file. If any error occurs in truncating or writing to the given file then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>file</name>
                     <description>The file that is truncated and written to if the output is different from the original.</description>
                     <type>QFile*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_original</name>
                  <description>The original content of the file that is used to compare the output once parsing is complete.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_input</name>
                  <description>Pointer to the input lines of the parsed source file. All parsing object's with the same root share this as a single resource where the root parser is responsible for allocating and destroying it.</description>
                  <type>QStringList*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_index</name>
                  <description>This stores the index pointing to the next input line to be processed. All parsing object's with the same root share this as a single resource where the root parser is responsible for allocating and destroying it.</description>
                  <type>int*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_indent</name>
                  <description>Pointer to the indent that is used for prepending spaces to all output lines when they are added. All parsing object's with the same root share this as a single resource where the root parser is responsible for allocating and destroying it.</description>
                  <type>int*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_output</name>
                  <description>Pointer to the output lines of the parsed file. All parsing object's with the same root share this as a single resource where the root parser is responsible for allocating and destroying it.</description>
                  <type>QStringList*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_root</name>
                  <description>Pointer to this parser object's root parser object. If this parser is the root then this is null.</description>
                  <type>AbstractParser*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_children</name>
                  <description>A list of pointers to all of this parser object's children.</description>
                  <type>QList&lt;AbstractParser*></type>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_child</name>
                  <description>Special pointer signal variable set by the step into child function. It is used to signal the process input function that it should step into the pointed to child parser object's process input function.</description>
                  <type>AbstractParser*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>AbstractParserFactory</name>
            <description>This represents the factory that can produce parser objects for a specific project type. It is a very simple class that has only one interface for producing new parser objects to parse individual source files.</description>
            <qtobject/>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>QObject</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>make</name>
                  <description>This interface makes a new parser object from the given file and and extension. This can return a null pointer in which case the source file is ignored and skipped.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractParser></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to new parser object or null pointer.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>name</name>
                     <description>Name of the source file that is parsed with the returned parser object.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>extension</name>
                     <description>Extension of the file that is parsed with the returned parser object.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>AbstractProjectFactory</name>
            <description>This represents the factory that provides all other factories and information to define a project type. A project type is defined as a specific programming language that a project references. This is a global singleton class so only one instance of this factory is available for the entire program. A new factory instance must be set at initialization of the program and should not be set again after that. To maintain backwards compatibility all previously defined project types must maintain the specific integer that defines them.</description>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>SingletonFactory&lt;AbstractProjectFactory></class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <destructor type="10">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>Virtual destructor so implemented classes have their destructor called correctly.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <default/>
                  <virtual/>
               </data>
            </destructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>size</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the number of project types that exist. Project types must be defined for all integers from 0 to one less than the number of project types returned by this interface.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Number of project types that exist.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>name</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the display name for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Display name for the given project type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose display name is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>defaultFilters</name>
                  <description>This interface returns the default filters for the scanning of source files the given project type possesses.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Default file filters for the given project type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose default file filters are returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeSettings</name>
                  <description>This interface makes a new settings dialog for the given project type. The settings dialog for a project type should contain all general settings for that project type, saving the settings in the qt settings class.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;QDialog></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to the new settings dialog for the given project type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose settings dialog is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>blockFactory</name>
                  <description>This interface returns a read only reference to the block factory for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>const AbstractBlockFactory&amp;</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Read only reference to block factory for the given project type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose block factory is returned as a reference.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeParserFactory</name>
                  <description>This interface makes a new parser factory for the given project type with the given block pointer as the root of an existing project to be parsed.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractParserFactory></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <abstract/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to created parser factory for the given project type.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose parser factory type is made and returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>root</name>
                     <description>Pointer to root block of existing project that will be parsed with the returned parser factory.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>ProjectFactory</name>
            <description>This implements the abstract project factory class that provides all factories and information needed for a project type.</description>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>AbstractProjectFactory</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <enumeration type="11">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>Defines all project types ending with the total size of all project types.</description>
               </data>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>CppQtType</name>
                     <description>Defines the C++/Qt project type.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>Total</name>
                     <description>Defines the total number of all project types.</description>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
            </enumeration>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>size</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns the number of project types that exist for the program.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Number of project types that exist.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>name</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns the display name for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Display name for the given project type.</return_description>
                  <operation>Return the display name of the given project type. If the given type does not exist then return an empty string.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose display name is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>defaultFilters</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns the default file filters for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Default file filters for the given project type.</return_description>
                  <operation>Return default file filters for the given project type. If the given type does not exist then return an empty string.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose default file filters are returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeSettings</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that makes a new settings dialog for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;QDialog></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to the new settings dialog for the given project type.</return_description>
                  <operation>Return a new settings dialog for the given project type. If the given type does not exist then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose settings dialog is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>blockFactory</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns a read only reference to the block factory for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>const AbstractBlockFactory&amp;</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Read only reference to block factory for the given project type.</return_description>
                  <operation>Return a reference to the block factory of the given project type. If the given project type does not exist then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose block factory is returned as a reference.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeParserFactory</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that makes a new parser factory for the given project type.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractParserFactory></type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to created parser factory for the given project type.</return_description>
                  <operation>Create a new parser factory for the given project type using the given block root. If the given project type does not exist then throw an exception.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>Project type whose parser factory type is made and returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>root</name>
                     <description>Pointer to root block of existing project that is used by returned parser object.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>BlockModel</name>
            <description>This implements the Qt abstract item model class and is used to model the tree structure of a project's block data. It only implements the interfaces necessary for read only functionality through Qt view classes. However the writable functionality exists with custom functions outside the Qt framework. The custom write operations supported are inserting blocks, moving blocks up and down, removing blocks, copying blocks, and cutting blocks.</description>
            <qtobject/>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>QAbstractItemModel</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <enumeration type="11">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>Role</name>
                  <description>Defines custom data roles this model uses for data changed signals.</description>
               </data>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>Name</name>
                     <description>Defines the name role which encompasses the title and icon of a block changing.</description>
                     <value>100</value>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
               <enumval type="12">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>Body</name>
                     <description>Defines the body role which encompasses the body of a block changing.</description>
                     <value>101</value>
                  </data>
               </enumval>
            </enumeration>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This constructs a new block model with the given root block and parent. Both the root block and parent can be given as null. A null root block means this model is empty.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <explicit/>
                  <operation>If the root given is not null then get the block type's block factory and connect the root block signals to this new block model.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>root</name>
                     <description>The root block this model will use for its data or null to make this model empty.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                     <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>The parent for this model.</description>
                     <type>QObject*</type>
                     <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </constructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>index</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns a a model index for the given row, column, and parent.</description>
                  <type>QModelIndex</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>A model index for the given row, column, and parent.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given row is less than 0 or the column is not 0 then return an invalid index.</operation>
                  <operation>Get the block pointer of the given parent index. If the given row is out of range of the parent block's list of children then return an invalid index.</operation>
                  <operation>Return a new index with the given row, column, and parent index.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>row</name>
                     <description>The row whose index is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>column</name>
                     <description>The column whose index is returned.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>The parent index of the index that is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>parent</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns the parent index of a given index.</description>
                  <type>QModelIndex</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Parent index of the given index.</return_description>
                  <operation>Get the pointer to the given index's parent block. If the parent block pointer is null or the parent's parent is null then return an invalid index.</operation>
                  <operation>Return the given index's parent index using the grandparent to get the parent's row.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>child</name>
                     <description>The index whose parent is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>rowCount</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns the number of rows the given index contains.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Number of rows the given index contains.</return_description>
                  <operation>If this model's root pointer is null then return 0, else return the number of children this index's block contains.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index whose contained number of rows is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>columnCount</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns the number of columns the given index contains. This model always contains 1 column regardless of index.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>This models column count is always 1.</return_description>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>The index is not used for this model because the number of columns is static.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>data</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that returns data for the given index with the given role. This model only implements the display and decoration roles.</description>
                  <type>QVariant</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <const/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <return_description>Data requested from given index and role. For this model this is a string or qt image.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given role is the display role then return the given index's block name, else if the given role is the decoration role then return the given index's block icon resized to this model's preferred icon size, else this is an unsupported role so return nothing.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index whose data is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>role</name>
                     <description>The role of the requested data.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>pointer</name>
                  <description>Returns the block pointer the given index represents in this model. If the given index is invalid this model's root block pointer is returned.</description>
                  <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Block pointer of the given index or the root block pointer if the index is invalid.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is valid return the given index's internal pointer recast as a block pointer, else it is invalid so return this model's root block pointer.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index whose block pointer is returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>insert</name>
                  <description>Inserts a new block into this model at the beginning of the given index's list of children.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <return_description>True on success or false on failure.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given block pointer is null then return false.</operation>
                  <operation>Prepend the given block pointer as a new child of the given index's block, signaling the model that a new row is being inserted and returning true for success.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index where the given block is inserted.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>block</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the block that is inserted into this model.</description>
                     <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock>&amp;&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>moveUp</name>
                  <description>Moves the given index up by one in the list of siblings it is part of. If the given index is already at row 0 then this does nothing. Returns the new index for the given index that was or was not moved.</description>
                  <type>QModelIndex</type>
                  <return_description>New index for the given index that was possibly moved.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index's row is already 0 then return the given index unchanged.</operation>
                  <operation>Move the block of the given index up by one in it's parent's list of children, signaling the model that the row is being moved. SPECIAL NOTE: the given index is destroyed when the begin move rows qt function is called.</operation>
                  <operation>Return a new index where the given index's block moved.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index that will possibly be moved up by 1.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>moveDown</name>
                  <description>Moves the given index down by one in the list of siblings it is part of. If the given index is already at the end of its list of siblings then this does nothing. Returns the new index for the given index that was or was not moved.</description>
                  <type>QModelIndex</type>
                  <return_description>New index for the given index that was possibly moved.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index's row is already at the end of its sibling list then return the given index unchanged.</operation>
                  <operation>Move the block of the given index down by one in it's parent's list of children, signaling the model that the row is being moved. SPECIAL NOTE: the given index is destroyed when the begin move rows qt function is called.</operation>
                  <operation>Return a new index where the given index's block moved.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index that will possibly be moved up by 1.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>remove</name>
                  <description>Removes the given index and its block for this model. If the index is not given this does nothing and returns false.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <return_description>True on success or false on failure.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is invalid then return false.</operation>
                  <operation>Remove the given index's block from its parent block, signaling the model that a row is being removed and returning true on success. SPECIAL NOTE: the given index is destroyed when the begin remove rows qt function is called.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index that is removed from this model.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>copy</name>
                  <description>Returns a pointer to a copy of the block at the given index. If the given index is not valid then a null pointer is returned.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to a copy of the given index or a null pointer if the given index is invalid.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is not valid then return a null pointer, else return a pointer to a new copy of the block at the given index.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The given index whose block is copied and returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>cut</name>
                  <description>Returns a pointer to the block at the given index, removing that index from the model but not deleting its block. Instead the ownership of the block is returned. If the given index is not valid then a null pointer is returned.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractBlock></type>
                  <return_description>Pointer to the block at the given index now removed or null pointer if the given index is not valid.</return_description>
                  <operation>If the given index is not valid then return a null pointer.</operation>
                  <operation>Take the child block at the given index from its parent block, signaling the model that a row is being removed and returning a smart pointer to the orphaned child block. SPECIAL NOTE: the given index is destroyed when the begin remove rows qt function is called.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The index that is removed from this model and its block returned.</description>
                     <type>const QModelIndex&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>factory</name>
                  <description>Returns a read only pointer to the block factory of the project type for this model's blocks. If the model is not set to any block data then a null pointer is returned.</description>
                  <type>const AbstractBlockFactory*</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Read only pointer to black factory for this model's block type or null pointer if this model is empty.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setRoot</name>
                  <description>Sets a new root block for this model's data. If the given pointer is null then this model is set to be empty with no data to represent.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Signal to the model that the beginning of a reset is happening.</operation>
                  <operation>If this model already has a root block pointer then disconnect all qt signals between this model and that root block.</operation>
                  <operation>Set this model's root block to the new pointer given and this model's block factory pointer to null. If the given new pointer is not null then set this model's block factory pointer to this block type's block factory and connect the root block signals to this object.</operation>
                  <operation>Signal to the model that the reset has finished.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newRoot</name>
                     <description>Pointer to root block that this model will use or null to set this model as empty.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private slots:</type>
            </data>
            <slot type="7">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>blockNameModified</name>
                  <description>Called when the root block contained within this model emits a name modified signal indicating a block with the given pointer within this model modified its name.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>block</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the block whose name has changed.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </slot>
            <slot type="7">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>blockBodyModified</name>
                  <description>Called when the root block contained within this model emits a body modified signal indicating a block with the given pointer within this model modified its body.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>block</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the block whose body has changed.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </slot>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>notifyChange</name>
                  <description>Determines the model index for the given block pointer and emits the data changed signal with that index and the given roles.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given block pointer has no parent then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Determine the index for the given block pointer within this model and emit the data changed signal with the found index and given roles.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>block</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the block whose index is found and used to emit data changed.</description>
                     <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>roles</name>
                     <description>The data roles used when emitting data changed.</description>
                     <type>const QVector&lt;int>&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_iconSize</name>
                  <description>The preferred icon size for indexes of this model when displayed in a view. This represents both the width and height.</description>
                  <constexpr/>
                  <static/>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <initializer>24</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_root</name>
                  <description>A pointer to the root block for this model's data. If this model is empty then this is null.</description>
                  <type>AbstractBlock*</type>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_factory</name>
                  <description>A read only pointer to this model block type's block factory. If this model is empty then this is null.</description>
                  <type>const AbstractBlockFactory*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>ScanThread</name>
            <description>This implements the qt thread class and is used to scan and parse an entire directory of source files with the given file filters and parser factory. This executes the scanning of files on the separate thread started by the qt thread class. Signals are emitted for the progress of the scanning and when it is complete. Because execution of parsing is done on a separate thread if an exception is thrown within that thread it is caught and saved within the class. This exception can be viewed from the main thread.</description>
            <qtobject/>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>QThread</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This constructs a new scan thread with the given parser factory, directory to scan, file filters, and possible parent.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <explicit/>
                  <operation>Set the given parser factory's parent to this scan thread and build a list of files that will be parsed in the given scan directory.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>factory</name>
                     <description>The parser factory that this scan thread will use to make all parser objects for each matched source file. This scan thread takes ownership of the factory.</description>
                     <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;AbstractParserFactory>&amp;&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>scanDirectory</name>
                     <description>The directory that this scan thread will scan for source files.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>filters</name>
                     <description>The file filters this scan thread will use for filtering the files in the given scan directory. Only files that match any of these filters will be parsed.</description>
                     <type>const QStringList&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parent</name>
                     <description>The parent of this object if any.</description>
                     <type>QObject*</type>
                     <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </constructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>size</name>
                  <description>Returns the total number of files that were matched for parsing.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Total number of files matched for parsing.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>hasException</name>
                  <description>Tests if an exception occurred in this scan thread's separate thread while parsing source files.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>True if an exception occurred else false it scanning was successful with no error.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>exception</name>
                  <description>Returns a reference to the exception that occurred in this scan thread's separate thread causing failure. If this scan thread has no exception this itself will throw an exception.</description>
                  <type>const Exception::Base&amp;</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Reference to exception that occurred while parsing source files.</return_description>
                  <operation>If this scan thread has no saved exception then throw an exception, else return a reference to the exception that occurred in this scan thread.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>signals:</type>
            </data>
            <signal type="8">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>progressChanged</name>
                  <description>Signals that the scan thread has started working on the given file index. The indexing starts at zero and ends at one less than the total number of files to process.</description>
                  <type></type>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>index</name>
                     <description>The current file index that is being parsed.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </signal>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>protected:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>run</name>
                  <description>This implements the interface that is called within the Qt thread when execution of that thread begins by calling the qt execute function. This implementation parses of all matched files from the given scan directory.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <virtual/>
                  <override/>
                  <final/>
                  <operation>Delete this scan thread's saved exception if any and set the pointer to null.</operation>
                  <operation>Iterate through this object's saved list of files to be parsed, emitting the progress changed signal for each index and parsing each file.</operation>
                  <operation>If any exception occurs while running this function then catch it and exit from this function immediately. If the exception is a Socrates one then save it to this scan thread's exception pointer else just report it to qt debug.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
         </access>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>private:</type>
            </data>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>buildList</name>
                  <description>Builds this scan thread's list of matched files that will be parsed from the given scan directory and file filters. A file must match only one file filter to be added to the list of matched files.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given directory does not exist then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Get a directory listing of all files and directories within it that match the given filters. Iterate through the list and add all matches that are not directories to this scan thread's list of matched files.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>scanDirectory</name>
                     <description>The directory where files will be matched and added to the list.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>filters</name>
                     <description>The filters that will be used to match files. Each string in this list must be a single filter.</description>
                     <type>const QStringList&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>run</name>
                  <description>Attempts to parse the given file is this object's parser factory makes a valid parser. This also checks if interruption is requested returning false if it is requested.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <return_description>False if interruption of this thread is requested or true otherwise.</return_description>
                  <operation>If interruption is requested then return false.</operation>
                  <operation>Make a new parser from this object's parser factory with the given file's information, saving it to the smart pointer _parser_. If _parser_ is not null then use it to parse the given file.</operation>
                  <operation>Return true signaling interruption is not requested and parsing should continue.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>info</name>
                     <description>Info for the file that may be parsed.</description>
                     <type>const QFileInfo&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>parse</name>
                  <description>Parses the given file using the given parser. If the file fails to open an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <static/>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Open the given file for reading and writing and interpreted as a text using the qt file device _file_. If opening the file fails then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Call the execute method of the given parser with the qt file _file_.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>parser</name>
                     <description>Pointer to the abstract parser that is used for parsing the given file.</description>
                     <type>AbstractParser*</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>info</name>
                     <description>Info for the file that is parsed with the given parser.</description>
                     <type>const QFileInfo&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_factory</name>
                  <description>A pointer to the parser factory this scan thread uses for making parser objects.</description>
                  <type>AbstractParserFactory*</type>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_list</name>
                  <description>A list of matched files that his scan thread parses.</description>
                  <type>QFileInfoList</type>
               </data>
            </variable>
            <variable type="1">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>_exception</name>
                  <description>A pointer that this scan thread uses to save any Socrates exception that occurs within its separate scanning thread.</description>
                  <type>Exception::Base*</type>
                  <initializer>nullptr</initializer>
               </data>
            </variable>
         </access>
      </class>
      <class type="4">
         <data version="1">
            <name>Project</name>
            <description>This is a single open project which contains everything for that project, watching the file it was opened or saved with for changes made by any outside source. If the file this project is associated with is changed by an outside source a signal is emitted. This class also provides all generic information of a project along with being able to edit it. This generic information includes the name, scan directory, and scan filters. The block model for this project's block tree data and the ability to create a scan thread object for scanning and parsing is also provided.</description>
            <qtobject/>
         </data>
         <parent type="13">
            <data version="2">
               <access>public</access>
               <class>QFileSystemWatcher</class>
            </data>
         </parent>
         <access type="5">
            <data version="1">
               <type>public:</type>
            </data>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This constructs a new project of the given type.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <explicit/>
                  <operation>Connect the file changed signal, create this project's root block, and set this project's file filters to the default for this project's type.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>type</name>
                     <description>The project type this new project is constructed as.</description>
                     <type>int</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </constructor>
            <constructor type="9">
               <data version="1">
                  <description>This constructs a project loaded from the file from the given path. If any error occurs from loading the project file an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type></type>
                  <explicit/>
                  <operation>Connect the file changed signal and get the contents of this project's file as a byte array.</operation>
                  <operation>Open a new Qt XML document with the byte array, reading in its contents for all required elements. If all required elements are not found then throw an exception, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>Read in the scan directory, type element, and root block along with all of its children blocks after creating a new block root.</operation>
                  <operation>Add this project's file path to the files being watched for changes and emit the saved signal.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>path</name>
                     <description>The path of the file that this project is loaded from.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </constructor>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>isNew</name>
                  <description>Tests if this is a new project that has not yet been saved to a file.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>True if this is a new unsaved project or false otherwise.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>isModified</name>
                  <description>Tests of this project has unsaved modifications.</description>
                  <type>bool</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>True if this project has unsaved content or false otherwise.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>type</name>
                  <description>Returns the project type for this project.</description>
                  <type>int</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>This project's type.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>path</name>
                  <description>Returns the path of the file associated with this open project. If this is a new project that has not been saved yet this returns an empty string.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Path to file associated with this project or an empty string.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>name</name>
                  <description>Returns the name of this project.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>The project's name.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>scanDirectory</name>
                  <description>Returns the scan directory path of this project in its canonical form.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Canonical path to this project's scan directory.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>scanFilters</name>
                  <description>Returns this project's file filters used for scanning of source files.</description>
                  <type>QString</type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>File filters used for this project's scanning.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>makeScanner</name>
                  <description>Makes and returns a pointer to a new scan thread that can be used for scanning and parsing matched source files in the scan directory of this project.</description>
                  <type>std::unique_ptr&lt;ScanThread></type>
                  <const/>
                  <return_description>Pointer to new scan thread object.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>model</name>
                  <description>Returns a pointer to the block model for this project used to edit the block data contained within it.</description>
                  <type>BlockModel*</type>
                  <return_description>Pointer to this project's block model.</return_description>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setName</name>
                  <description>Sets a new name for this project with the given name.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given new name is different than this project's current name then set this project's name to the new name given, emit the name changed signal, and signal this project has been modified.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newName</name>
                     <description>The new name this project's name is set to.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setScanDirectory</name>
                  <description>Sets a new scan directory path for this project to the given path. The given path can be relative to this program's present working directory. If the given path is not a valid directory then an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given path is the same as this project's current scan directory path then return.</operation>
                  <operation>If the given new path is not a valid directory then throw an exception.</operation>
                  <operation>Set this project's scan directory to the new path given in its canonical form and signal this project has been modified.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newPath</name>
                     <description>Path that this project's scan directory is set to.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>setScanFilters</name>
                  <description>Sets new scanning file filters for this project. These filters are used to filter out what files are matched for parsing when a scan thread of this project is used. The filter filters must be separated by spaces.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If the given scan filters is different than this project's current scan filters then set this project's scan filters to the new filters given and signal this project has been modified.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>newFilters</name>
                     <description>The file filters that this project will use for scanning.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>save</name>
                  <description>Saves this project to its associated file. If this is a new project that has never been saved then an exception is thrown. If any writing error occurs while saving an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>If this project has no path to save to then throw an exception, else go to the next step.</operation>
                  <operation>Create a new Qt XML document, appending its XML processing instructions and creating the root project element.</operation>
                  <operation>Save this project's basic information, its type element, and its root block along with all children blocks to the project element.</operation>
                  <operation>Save the Qt XML document as a byte array and save the byte array to this project's file, setting this project as not modified and emitting the saved signal.</operation>
               </data>
            </function>
            <function type="2">
               <data version="1">
                  <name>saveAs</name>
                  <description>Saves this project to a new file with the given path. If any writing error occurs while saving an exception is thrown.</description>
                  <type>void</type>
                  <operation>Save this project's current file path to _oldPath_, set this project's file path to the new path given, and then call this project's save method.</operation>
                  <operation>If any exception is caught while saving then revert this project and its file watcher back to the old path and throw the caught exception.</operation>
                  <operation>If _oldPath_ is not empty then remove the path from this file watcher. Add the new path to this file watcher.</operation>
               </data>
               <variable type="1">
                  <data version="1">
                     <name>path</name>
                     <description>The path to the new file this project is saved to.</description>
                     <type>const QString&amp;</type>
                  </data>
               </variable>
            </function>
         </access>
